@node Adding abbreviations
@section Adding abbreviations

@findex abbrev-extras-add-mode-abbrev
The command @code{abbrev-extras-add-mode-abbrev} lets you define a mode-specific abbreviation in three steps. It prompts for:

@enumerate
@item
A major mode, with completion over all functions ending in @samp{-mode}.
@item
The abbreviation string (the short form you will type).
@item
The expansion string (the text it should expand to).
@end enumerate

The command determines the correct abbrev table name by appending @samp{-abbrev-table} to the selected mode name (for example, @code{org-mode-abbrev-table} for @code{org-mode}). If that table does not yet exist, it is created automatically. The abbreviation is then defined using @code{define-abbrev}.

When @code{abbrev-extras-write-file-p} is non-nil (@ref{@code{abbrev-extras-write-file-p}}), the full set of abbreviation definitions is written to @code{abbrev-file-name} immediately after adding the new entry.

@node Writing abbreviations
@section Writing abbreviations

@findex abbrev-extras-write-abbrevs
The command @code{abbrev-extras-write-abbrevs} saves all abbreviation definitions (both global and mode-specific) to the file specified by @code{abbrev-file-name}. This is a thin wrapper around @code{write-abbrev-file} that also displays a confirmation message.

Use this command when @code{abbrev-extras-write-file-p} is set to @code{nil} and you want to persist your accumulated changes, or at any time to ensure the abbrev file is up to date.

@node Functions
@chapter Functions

@menu
* Abbreviation table management::
@end menu

@node Abbreviation table management
@section Abbreviation table management

@findex abbrev-extras-get-sorted-modes
@findex abbrev-extras-add-abbrev-to-table
@findex abbrev-extras-maybe-create-abbrev-table
Three helper functions support the main command:

@itemize
@item
@code{abbrev-extras-get-sorted-modes} scans the obarray for all functions whose names end in @samp{-mode} and returns a sorted list of their names. This provides the completion candidates for @code{abbrev-extras-add-mode-abbrev} (@ref{Adding abbreviations}).

@item
@code{abbrev-extras-add-abbrev-to-table} defines an abbreviation in a given table, creating the table first if needed via @code{abbrev-extras-maybe-create-abbrev-table}.

@item
@code{abbrev-extras-maybe-create-abbrev-table} checks whether a table symbol is bound and, if not, creates an empty abbrev table for it using @code{define-abbrev-table}.
@end itemize

